info.title: PlayFab Events API
info.description: Write custom PlayStream and Telemetry events for any PlayFab entity. Telemetry events can be used for analytic, reporting, or debugging. PlayStream events can do all of that and also trigger custom actions in near real-time.

post.description: Creates a new telemetry key for the title.
Deletes a telemetry key configured for the title.
Gets information about a telemetry key configured for the title.
Lists all telemetry keys configured for the title.
Sets a telemetry key to the active or deactivated state.
Write batches of entity based events to PlayStream. The namespace of the Event must be 'custom' or start with 'custom.'.
Write batches of entity based events to as Telemetry events (bypass PlayStream). The namespace must be 'custom' or start with 'custom.'
post.x-requestDetails: This API must be called with either X-EntityToken or X-TelemetryKey headers. If sending X-EntityToken the value must be a valid EntityToken for your title. If using X-TelemetryKey the value must be a Telemetry Key configured for your title set to 'Active'. If both are provided, X-TelemetryKey will be ignored.

ApiErrorWrapper.description: The basic wrapper around every failed API response

errorDetails.description: Detailed description of individual issues with the request object

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Entity.description: The optional entity to perform this action on. Defaults to the currently logged in entity.

KeyName.description: The name of the new key. Telemetry key names must be unique within the scope of the title.

NewKeyDetails.description: Details about the newly created telemetry key.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Entity.description: The optional entity to perform this action on. Defaults to the currently logged in entity.

KeyName.description: The name of the key to delete.

WasKeyDeleted.description: Indicates whether or not the key was deleted. If false, no key with that name existed.

EntityKey.description: Combined entity type and ID structure which uniquely identifies a single entity.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the event (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.). Before an event is written, this collection and the base request custom tags will be merged, but not overriden. This enables the caller to specify static tags and per event tags.

Entity.description: Entity associated with the event. If null, the event will apply to the calling entity.

EventNamespace.description: The namespace in which the event is defined. Allowed namespaces can vary by API.

OriginalId.description: The original unique identifier associated with this event before it was posted to PlayFab. The value might differ from the EventId value, which is assigned when the event is received by the server.

OriginalTimestamp.description: The time (in UTC) associated with this event when it occurred. If specified, this value is stored in the OriginalTimestamp property of the PlayStream event.

Payload.description: Arbitrary data associated with the event. Only one of Payload or PayloadJSON is allowed.

PayloadJSON.description: Arbitrary data associated with the event, represented as a JSON serialized string. Only one of Payload or PayloadJSON is allowed.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Entity.description: The optional entity to perform this action on. Defaults to the currently logged in entity.

KeyName.description: The name of the key to retrieve.

KeyDetails.description: Details about the requested telemetry key.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Entity.description: The optional entity to perform this action on. Defaults to the currently logged in entity.

KeyDetails.description: The telemetry keys configured for the title.

Active.description: Whether to set the key to active (true) or deactivated (false).

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Entity.description: The optional entity to perform this action on. Defaults to the currently logged in entity.

KeyName.description: The name of the key to update.

KeyDetails.description: The most current details about the telemetry key that was to be updated.

WasKeyUpdated.description: Indicates whether or not the key was updated. If false, the key was already in the desired state.

IsActive.description: Whether or not the key is currently active. Deactivated keys cannot be used for telemetry ingestion.

KeyValue.description: The key that can be distributed to clients for use during telemetry ingestion.

LastUpdateTime.description: When the key was last updated.

Name.description: The name of the key. Telemetry key names are unique within the scope of the title.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Events.description: The collection of events to write. Up to 200 events can be written per request.

AssignedEventIds.description: The unique identifiers assigned by the server to the events, in the same order as the events in the request. Only returned if FlushToPlayStream option is true.
